Preheat the oven to 200°C. Fill and boil your kettle. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Chop each half into three pieces. Trim the @courgette{1}, then halve lengthways and chop into roughly 1cm wide 5cm long batons. Halve the @radishes{100}. Crumble the @feta cheese{100} into small pieces and set aside.

Pop the red onion, courgette, radishes and @British chicken thighs{2} on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, and sprinkle on the @chermoula spice mix{1}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want everything nicely spread out.

Pour the @water{240%ml} for the bulgur wheat into a #saucepan{} with the @chicken stock powder{1} and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop them in a #bowl{}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Add half of the parsley to the tomatoes along with the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Set aside.

Once the bulgur is cooked add the remaining chopped parsley and mix through. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Once your chicken and veg are cooked, remove from the oven.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Use two forks to pull the chicken apart into chunky shredded pieces (you can do this in the tray).

Divide the bulgur between plates and top with equal portions of chicken, roasted veggies and tomato salad. Finish off with a crumble of feta and enjoy!